sections.text:
Inclusion criteria for the review were defined as follows:
 study performed in humans; published since 2015, in English in peer-reviewed journals; the concentration of bisphenols (BPA and/or BPS and/or BPF) was determined in urine samples collected from the mother at least once during pregnancy or from children; the relationship between prenatal and/or postnatal exposure to selected bisphenols (BPA and/or BPS and/or BPF) and the occurrence of allergic diseases in children was assessed; the occurrence of the following health effects in children was assessed: asthma, wheezing, eczema/atopic dermatitis, aeroallergies, allergic rhinitis; results were given as odds ratio (OR), relative risk (RR) or hazard ratio (HR) with the corresponding 95% confidence intervals (95% CIs).

